 ### Outcome mapping
 
-The three `SchedulerDecision` outcomes map to apparatus actions:
+The three `SchedulerDecision` outcomes map to apparatus actions
+applied per-tick. Every row written by the tick stamps the
+triggering `clockworks.timer` event id into `tickEventId`.
 
 | Outcome   | Phase transition       | Reckonings row | Notes |
 |-----------|------------------------|----------------|-------|
 | `approve` | `new` → active target  | `accepted`     | The target is the writ-type config's active state; weight (if present) is threaded onto the row. |
-| `defer`   | none                   | none           | The writ stays in `new`; absence of a row is itself a signal. |
+| `defer`   | none                   | `deferred`     | The writ stays in `new`; the row carries `deferReason: 'other'` and the decision's `reason` in `deferNote`. Other defer-metadata fields (`deferUntil`, `deferSignal`, `deferCount`) stay absent in v0. |
 | `decline` | `new` → `cancelled`    | `declined`     | The decision's `reason` is recorded as the writ's resolution string; the row carries `declineReason: 'other'` and the reason in `remediationHint`. |
 
 ### Failure modes
 
+The tick handler is the only path into the scheduler call site.
+Per-fire failure modes:
+
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started`                                  | Throws fail-loud (`[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved`). Production never trips this; test fixtures use it as a deterministic loud signal. |
+| Empty held-petition set (no writs in `new` carrying `ext.reckoner`) | Early-return after the held-writs query. No scheduler call, no rows, no errors. |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | Writ excluded from the candidate set before `SchedulerInput` is built. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] tick: scheduler "<id>" validateConfig threw …` prefix; the entire tick is skipped (no rows, no transitions). |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped. |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; the in-scope decisions still apply. |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the **entire tick** is skipped — no decisions for any writ in the fire are applied. |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; that one decision is ignored. |
 
